      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THERESHEWAS (3) modest result two starts ago at Bathurst then again didn't measure up at her latest appearance over 1690m at this track, beaten 7 metres into sixth after being handy in the run. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Tackles a similar assignment and she can turn in a much better performance. ELIZAJANE (4) finished third last start over 1690m at this track, beaten a head. That was an improvement on the unplaced effort at this track the run before. Meets a similar line up and she is capable of another bold performance. MASTER MIKI (9) is also high on the list of contenders despite a tough draw. Best form measures up favourably in this line-up so just needs a bit of luck to go his way. WILL HE REIGN (11) cannot be ruled out but needs a bit of luck from the tricky draw.",
